<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9738307-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s5004"><num value="5004">§ 5004.</num><heading> Discontinuance of service on post roads</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Postal Service may discontinue service on a post road or part thereof when, in its opinion, the public interest so requires.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9738308-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/767">84 Stat. 767</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb9738309-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb973830a-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb973830b-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1971-07-01">July 1, 1971</date>, pursuant to Resolution No. 71–9 of the Board of Governors. See <ref href="/us/pl/91/375/s15/a">section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, set out as a note preceding <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
